            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Museum ¶ Melbourne, 19 April 1878 ¶ Dear Father! ¶  ¶ [not relevant] ¶  ¶ … I thought I had informed you dear Father about my work before. The Baron von Mueller is an arrogant, rude man, but t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">M78.04.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Georg Luehmann to Johann Christian Luehmann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold; "
               xml:lang="de">German text to be transcribed.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold; "
               xml:lang="de">Translation [presumably by owner of MS].</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Botanic Museum</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 19 April 1878</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Father!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[not relevant]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>… I thought I had informed you dear Father about my work before. The Baron von Mueller is an arrogant, rude man, but there is no equal anywhere in the world, so they say, as far as Botanical knowledge is concerned. He is unpopular with the workers and the public in general. It has got so bad that even the papers have written against him. So they had to dismiss him from the Gardens, but being in a Government job, in conjunction with Germany, they had to keep him on as an "Botaniker Consultant" on full salary. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I myself have bettered my position now. I work now in this building called "Museum" and I have to attend to different plants, sorting them out and do bookwork about them. I am not too good at it, as I find it a bit late to study about this at my age,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Page missing.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">following letters do not mention M. </seg>
                  </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>26 March 1884: he says that Groener died last month. He had become an alcoholic 'as so many are doing here'. G's 'work boss' [is that M?] had sent him to WA but he died on the way.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The last letter is dated 22 November 1898.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
